#. <section class="sutta" id="sn46.52"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn46.52:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 46"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 46"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn46.52:0.2"
msgid "6. Sākacchavagga"
msgstr "6. Discussion"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn46.52:0.3"
msgid "52. Pariyāyasutta"
msgstr "52. Is There a Way?"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli5.108"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.52:1.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya "
"sāvatthiṃ piṇḍāya pavisiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"Then several mendicants robed up in the morning and, taking their bowls and "
"robes, entered Sāvatthī for alms."

msgctxt "sn46.52:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then those mendicants thought:"

msgctxt "sn46.52:1.3"
msgid "“atippago kho tāva sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya carituṃ."
msgstr "“It’s too early to wander for alms in Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn46.52:1.4"
msgid ""
"Yannūna mayaṃ yena aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ ārāmo "
"tenupasaṅkameyyāmā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Why don’t we go to the monastery of the wanderers who follow other paths?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.52:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū yena aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ ārāmo "
"tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā tehi aññatitthiyehi paribbājakehi saddhiṃ "
"sammodiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"Then they went to the monastery of the wanderers who follow other paths, and "
"exchanged greetings with the wanderers there."

msgctxt "sn46.52:2.2"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinne kho te bhikkhū aññatitthiyā paribbājakā etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, they sat down to one "
"side. The wanderers said to them:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.52:3.1"
msgid "“Samaṇo, āvuso, gotamo sāvakānaṃ evaṃ dhammaṃ deseti:"
msgstr "“Reverends, the ascetic Gotama teaches his disciples like this:"

msgctxt "sn46.52:3.2"
msgid ""
"‘etha tumhe, bhikkhave, pañca nīvaraṇe pahāya cetaso upakkilese paññāya "
"dubbalīkaraṇe satta bojjhaṅge yathābhūtaṃ bhāvethā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Mendicants, please give up the five hindrances—corruptions of the heart "
"that weaken wisdom—and truly develop the seven awakening factors.’"

msgctxt "sn46.52:3.3"
msgid "Mayampi kho, āvuso, sāvakānaṃ evaṃ dhammaṃ desema:"
msgstr "We too teach our disciples:"

msgctxt "sn46.52:3.4"
msgid ""
"‘etha tumhe, āvuso, pañca nīvaraṇe pahāya cetaso upakkilese paññāya "
"dubbalīkaraṇe satta bojjhaṅge yathābhūtaṃ bhāvethā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Reverends, please give up the five hindrances—corruptions of the heart that "
"weaken wisdom—and truly develop the seven awakening factors.’"

msgctxt "sn46.52:3.5"
msgid ""
"Idha no, āvuso, ko viseso, ko adhippayāso, kiṃ nānākaraṇaṃ samaṇassa vā "
"gotamassa amhākaṃ vā, yadidaṃ—dhammadesanāya vā dhammadesanaṃ, anusāsaniyā "
"vā anusāsanin”ti?"
msgstr ""
"What, then, is the difference between the ascetic Gotama’s teaching and "
"instruction and ours?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli5.109"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.52:4.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ bhāsitaṃ neva "
"abhinandiṃsu nappaṭikkosiṃsu;"
msgstr ""
"Those mendicants neither approved nor dismissed that statement of the "
"wanderers who follow other paths."

msgctxt "sn46.52:4.2"
msgid "anabhinanditvā appaṭikkositvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkamiṃsu:"
msgstr "They got up from their seat, thinking:"

msgctxt "sn46.52:4.3"
msgid "“bhagavato santike etassa bhāsitassa atthaṃ ājānissāmā”ti."
msgstr "“We will learn the meaning of this statement from the Buddha himself.”"

msgctxt "sn46.52:4.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū sāvatthiṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ "
"piṇḍapātapaṭikkantā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ "
"abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū "
"bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"Then, after the meal, when they returned from alms-round, they went up to "
"the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what had happened."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.52:5.1"
msgid ""
"“Idha mayaṃ, bhante, pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiṃ "
"piṇḍāya pavisimha."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn46.52:5.2"
msgid "Tesaṃ no, bhante, amhākaṃ etadahosi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn46.52:5.3"
msgid "‘atippago kho tāva sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya carituṃ, "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn46.52:5.4"
msgid ""
"yannūna mayaṃ yena aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ ārāmo "
"tenupasaṅkameyyāmā’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn46.52:5.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho mayaṃ, bhante, yena aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ ārāmo "
"tenupasaṅkamimha; upasaṅkamitvā tehi aññatitthiyehi paribbājakehi saddhiṃ "
"sammodimha."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn46.52:5.6"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdimha. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinne kho amhe, bhante, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.52:6.1"
msgid ""
"‘Samaṇo, āvuso, gotamo sāvakānaṃ evaṃ dhammaṃ deseti “etha tumhe, bhikkhave, "
"pañca nīvaraṇe pahāya cetaso upakkilese paññāya dubbalīkaraṇe satta "
"bojjhaṅge yathābhūtaṃ bhāvethā”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn46.52:6.2"
msgid "Mayampi kho, āvuso, sāvakānaṃ evaṃ dhammaṃ desema:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn46.52:6.3"
msgid ""
"“etha tumhe, āvuso, pañca nīvaraṇe pahāya cetaso upakkilese paññāya "
"dubbalīkaraṇe satta bojjhaṅge yathābhūtaṃ bhāvethā”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn46.52:6.4"
msgid ""
"Idha no, āvuso, ko viseso, ko adhippayāso, kiṃ nānākaraṇaṃ samaṇassa vā "
"gotamassa amhākaṃ vā, yadidaṃ—dhammadesanāya vā dhammadesanaṃ, anusāsaniyā "
"vā anusāsanin’ti?"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.52:7.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho mayaṃ, bhante, tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ bhāsitaṃ neva "
"abhinandimha nappaṭikkosimha, anabhinanditvā appaṭikkositvā uṭṭhāyāsanā "
"pakkamimha:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn46.52:7.2"
msgid "‘bhagavato santike etassa bhāsitassa atthaṃ ājānissāmā’”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.52:8.1"
msgid "“Evaṃvādino, bhikkhave, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evamassu vacanīyā:"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, when wanderers who follow other paths say this, you should say "
"to them:"

msgctxt "sn46.52:8.2"
msgid ""
"‘atthi panāvuso, pariyāyo, yaṃ pariyāyaṃ āgamma pañca nīvaraṇā dasa honti, "
"satta bojjhaṅgā catuddasā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘But reverends, is there a way in which the five hindrances become ten and "
"the seven awakening factors become fourteen?’"

msgctxt "sn46.52:8.3"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ puṭṭhā, bhikkhave, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā na ceva sampāyissanti, "
"uttariñca vighātaṃ āpajjissanti."
msgstr ""
"Questioned like this, the wanderers who follow other paths would be stumped, "
"and, in addition, would get frustrated."

msgctxt "sn46.52:8.4"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "sn46.52:8.5"
msgid "Yathā taṃ, bhikkhave, avisayasmiṃ."
msgstr "Because they’re out of their element."

msgctxt "sn46.52:8.6"
msgid ""
"Nāhaṃ taṃ, bhikkhave, passāmi sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake "
"sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya, yo imesaṃ pañhānaṃ veyyākaraṇena "
"cittaṃ ārādheyya, aññatra tathāgatena vā tathāgatasāvakena vā ito vā pana "
"sutvā."
msgstr ""
"I don’t see anyone in this world—with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this "
"population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans—who could "
"provide a satisfying answer to these questions except for the Realized One "
"or his disciple or someone who has heard it from them."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli5.110"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.52:9.1"
msgid ""
"Katamo ca, bhikkhave, pariyāyo, yaṃ pariyāyaṃ āgamma pañca nīvaraṇā dasa "
"honti?"
msgstr "And what is the way in which the five hindrances become ten?"

msgctxt "sn46.52:9.2"
msgid ""
"Yadapi, bhikkhave, ajjhattaṃ kāmacchando tadapi nīvaraṇaṃ, yadapi bahiddhā "
"kāmacchando tadapi nīvaraṇaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Sensual desire for what is internal is a hindrance; and sensual desire for "
"what is external is also a hindrance."

msgctxt "sn46.52:9.3"
msgid ""
"‘Kāmacchandanīvaraṇan’ti iti hidaṃ uddesaṃ gacchati. Tadamināpetaṃ "
"pariyāyena dvayaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how what is concisely referred to as ‘the hindrance of sensual desire’"
" becomes twofold. "

msgctxt "sn46.52:9.4"
msgid ""
"Yadapi, bhikkhave, ajjhattaṃ byāpādo tadapi nīvaraṇaṃ, yadapi bahiddhā "
"byāpādo tadapi nīvaraṇaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Ill will for what is internal is a hindrance; and ill will for what is "
"external is also a hindrance."

msgctxt "sn46.52:9.5"
msgid ""
"‘Byāpādanīvaraṇan’ti iti hidaṃ uddesaṃ gacchati. Tadamināpetaṃ pariyāyena "
"dvayaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how what is concisely referred to as ‘the hindrance of ill will’ "
"becomes twofold. "

msgctxt "sn46.52:9.6"
msgid ""
"Yadapi, bhikkhave, thinaṃ tadapi nīvaraṇaṃ, yadapi middhaṃ tadapi nīvaraṇaṃ."
msgstr "Dullness is a hindrance; and drowsiness is also a hindrance."

msgctxt "sn46.52:9.7"
msgid ""
"‘Thinamiddhanīvaraṇan’ti iti hidaṃ uddesaṃ gacchati. Tadamināpetaṃ "
"pariyāyena dvayaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how what is concisely referred to as ‘the hindrance of dullness and "
"drowsiness’ becomes twofold. "

msgctxt "sn46.52:9.8"
msgid ""
"Yadapi, bhikkhave, uddhaccaṃ tadapi nīvaraṇaṃ, yadapi kukkuccaṃ tadapi "
"nīvaraṇaṃ."
msgstr "Restlessness is a hindrance; and remorse is also a hindrance."

msgctxt "sn46.52:9.9"
msgid ""
"‘Uddhaccakukkuccanīvaraṇan’ti iti hidaṃ uddesaṃ gacchati. Tadamināpetaṃ "
"pariyāyena dvayaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how what is concisely referred to as ‘the hindrance of restlessness "
"and remorse’ becomes twofold. "

# Dhammesu is used here, unlike in the previous phrases. This shift is not reflected in BB’s translation.
msgctxt "sn46.52:9.10"
msgid ""
"Yadapi, bhikkhave, ajjhattaṃ dhammesu vicikicchā tadapi nīvaraṇaṃ, yadapi "
"bahiddhā dhammesu vicikicchā tadapi nīvaraṇaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Doubt about internal things is a hindrance; and doubt about external things "
"is also a hindrance."

msgctxt "sn46.52:9.11"
msgid ""
"‘Vicikicchānīvaraṇan’ti iti hidaṃ uddesaṃ gacchati. Tadamināpetaṃ pariyāyena "
"dvayaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how what is concisely referred to as ‘the hindrance of doubt’ becomes "
"twofold. "

msgctxt "sn46.52:9.12"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pariyāyo, yaṃ pariyāyaṃ āgamma pañca nīvaraṇā dasa "
"honti."
msgstr "This is the way in which the five hindrances become ten."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.52:10.1"
msgid ""
"Katamo ca, bhikkhave, pariyāyo, yaṃ pariyāyaṃ āgamma satta bojjhaṅgā "
"catuddasa honti?"
msgstr ""
"And what is the way in which the seven awakening factors become fourteen?"

msgctxt "sn46.52:10.2"
msgid ""
"Yadapi, bhikkhave, ajjhattaṃ dhammesu sati tadapi satisambojjhaṅgo, yadapi "
"bahiddhā dhammesu sati tadapi satisambojjhaṅgo."
msgstr ""
"Mindfulness of internal things is the awakening factor of mindfulness; and "
"mindfulness of external things is also the awakening factor of mindfulness."

msgctxt "sn46.52:10.3"
msgid ""
"‘Satisambojjhaṅgo’ti iti hidaṃ uddesaṃ gacchati. Tadamināpetaṃ pariyāyena "
"dvayaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how what is concisely referred to as ‘the awakening factor of "
"mindfulness’ becomes twofold. "

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli5.111"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
#. VAR: pavicinati → pavicināti (mr)
msgctxt "sn46.52:11.1"
msgid ""
"Yadapi, bhikkhave, ajjhattaṃ dhammesu paññāya pavicinati pavicarati "
"parivīmaṃsamāpajjati tadapi dhammavicayasambojjhaṅgo, yadapi bahiddhā "
"dhammesu paññāya pavicinati pavicarati parivīmaṃsamāpajjati tadapi "
"dhammavicayasambojjhaṅgo."
msgstr ""
"Investigating, exploring, and inquiring into internal things with wisdom is "
"the awakening factor of investigation of principles; and investigating, "
"exploring, and inquiring into external things with wisdom is also the "
"awakening factor of investigation of principles."

msgctxt "sn46.52:11.2"
msgid ""
"‘Dhammavicayasambojjhaṅgo’ti iti hidaṃ uddesaṃ gacchati. Tadamināpetaṃ "
"pariyāyena dvayaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how what is concisely referred to as ‘the awakening factor of "
"investigation of principles’ becomes twofold. "

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.52:12.1"
msgid ""
"Yadapi, bhikkhave, kāyikaṃ vīriyaṃ tadapi vīriyasambojjhaṅgo, yadapi "
"cetasikaṃ vīriyaṃ tadapi vīriyasambojjhaṅgo."
msgstr ""
"Physical energy is the awakening factor of energy; and mental energy is also "
"the awakening factor of energy."

msgctxt "sn46.52:12.2"
msgid ""
"‘Vīriyasambojjhaṅgo’ti iti hidaṃ uddesaṃ gacchati. Tadamināpetaṃ pariyāyena "
"dvayaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how what is concisely referred to as ‘the awakening factor of energy’ "
"becomes twofold. "

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.52:13.1"
msgid ""
"Yadapi, bhikkhave, savitakkasavicārā pīti tadapi pītisambojjhaṅgo, yadapi "
"avitakkaavicārā pīti tadapi pītisambojjhaṅgo."
msgstr ""
"Rapture while placing the mind and keeping it connected is the awakening "
"factor of rapture; and rapture without placing the mind and keeping it "
"connected is also the awakening factor of rapture."

msgctxt "sn46.52:13.2"
msgid ""
"‘Pītisambojjhaṅgo’ti iti hidaṃ uddesaṃ gacchati. Tadamināpetaṃ pariyāyena "
"dvayaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"In this way what is concisely referred to as ‘the awakening factor of "
"rapture’ becomes twofold. "

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.52:14.1"
msgid ""
"Yadapi, bhikkhave, kāyappassaddhi tadapi passaddhisambojjhaṅgo, yadapi "
"cittappassaddhi tadapi passaddhisambojjhaṅgo."
msgstr ""
"Physical tranquility is the awakening factor of tranquility; and mental "
"tranquility is also the awakening factor of tranquility."

msgctxt "sn46.52:14.2"
msgid ""
"‘Passaddhisambojjhaṅgo’ti iti hidaṃ uddesaṃ gacchati. Tadamināpetaṃ "
"pariyāyena dvayaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"In this way what is concisely referred to as ‘the awakening factor of "
"tranquility’ becomes twofold. "

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.52:15.1"
msgid ""
"Yadapi, bhikkhave, savitakko savicāro samādhi tadapi samādhisambojjhaṅgo, "
"yadapi avitakkaavicāro samādhi tadapi samādhisambojjhaṅgo."
msgstr ""
"Immersion while placing the mind and keeping it connected is the awakening "
"factor of immersion; and immersion without placing the mind and keeping it "
"connected is also the awakening factor of immersion."

msgctxt "sn46.52:15.2"
msgid ""
"‘Samādhisambojjhaṅgo’ti iti hidaṃ uddesaṃ gacchati. Tadamināpetaṃ pariyāyena "
"dvayaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"In this way what is concisely referred to as ‘the awakening factor of "
"immersion’ becomes twofold. "

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.52:16.1"
msgid ""
"Yadapi, bhikkhave, ajjhattaṃ dhammesu upekkhā tadapi upekkhāsambojjhaṅgo, "
"yadapi bahiddhā dhammesu upekkhā tadapi upekkhāsambojjhaṅgo."
msgstr ""
"Equanimity for internal things is the awakening factor of equanimity; and "
"equanimity for external things is also the awakening factor of equanimity."

msgctxt "sn46.52:16.2"
msgid ""
"‘Upekkhāsambojjhaṅgo’ti iti hidaṃ uddesaṃ gacchati. Tadamināpetaṃ pariyāyena "
"dvayaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"In this way what is concisely referred to as ‘the awakening factor of "
"equanimity’ becomes twofold. "

msgctxt "sn46.52:16.3"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pariyāyo, yaṃ pariyāyaṃ āgamma satta bojjhaṅgā "
"catuddasā”ti."
msgstr "This is the way in which the seven awakening factors become fourteen.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn46.52:16.4"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
